    <p>Large-scale Drupal sites often maintain a separate "staging" server to test and preview changes before they're released to the public. If you're working on a smaller project, though, it can be useful to give a few trusted testers access to a few pages of the site. In those situations, the <a href="https://drupal.org/project/protected_pages">Protected Pages</a> module might be just what you need.</p>

